  "prompt": "How can I use two WhatsApp accounts with the same number on different devices?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, WhatsApp does not natively support using the same phone number on multiple devices simultaneously. However, there are a few workarounds:\n\n1. WhatsApp Web/Desktop\n- Use WhatsApp Web or Desktop alongside the mobile app\n- Keep your primary account on your phone\n- Access a secondary view on computer\n\n2. WhatsApp Business + Personal Account\n- Create a WhatsApp Business account\n- Use this alongside your personal account\n- Requires different app installation\n\n3. Dual/Clone App Methods\n- Use app cloning features on Android (like App Cloner)\n- Some Android phones have built-in dual app functionality\n- Allows running two WhatsApp instances\n\n4. Third-Party Apps\n- Some apps claim to enable multi-device WhatsApp\n- Be cautious of potential security risks\n- Not officially supported by WhatsApp\n\n5. WhatsApp Multi-Device Beta\n- WhatsApp is developing a multi-device feature\n- Currently in limited beta testing\n- Allows use on multiple devices without phone connection\n\n6. SIM Card Switching\n- Use a dual SIM phone\n- Switch between numbers/accounts\n\nOfficial multi-device support is evolving, so check WhatsApp's latest features for the most current options.",
